properties.scriptBody:
@echo off

 set pp=%date:~7,2%_%date:~4,2%_%date:~10,4%_%time:~0,2%_%time:~3,2%_%time:~6,2%

 set p=%pp: =0%

 echo spool ${p:component/SpoolDirectory}\${p:ExecuteScriptDriver}_%p%.txt >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"

 echo select sys_context('userenv','db_name') as Database from dual; >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo select user as Username,TO_CHAR (SYSTIMESTAMP, 'DD-MON-YYYY HH24:MI:SS') AS Execution_Date_Time from dual;  >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"

 echo set echo on; >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
  
 echo /* ==================================================================================  >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo					Invalid objects before execution        	      >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo	 ==================================================================================  */  >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo select count(*) as Invalid_Count from user_objects where status='INVALID'; >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 
 echo select object_name,object_type,status,created,last_ddl_time from user_objects where status='INVALID'; >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 
 echo /* **********************************************************************************  >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo    				Execution Started				     >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo    ********************************************************************************** */ >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 
 echo @${p:ExecuteScriptDriver} >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 
 echo  /*  **********************************************************************************  >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo    				Execution Ended					       >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo    **********************************************************************************  */>> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 
 echo /* ==================================================================================  >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo					Invalid objects after execution 		     >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo	 ==================================================================================  */  >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo select count(*) as Invalid_Count from user_objects where status='INVALID'; >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo select object_name,object_type,status,created,last_ddl_time from user_objects where status='INVALID'; >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 
 
 echo spool off >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"
 echo set echo off; >> "ExecuteScript_spool.sql"

properties.scriptBody:
cd ${p:TCLS_Path1}

if [ -d "tmp" ]
then
echo "tmp folder exists"
echo "Taking Backup of tmp Folder....!"
mv tmp tmp_$(date +%d-%m-%Y_%H.%M.%S)
echo "Backup of tmp folder taken successfully....!"
else
echo "tmp folder does not exists"
fi

if [ -d "cache" ]
then
echo "cache folder exist"
echo "Taking Backup of cache Folder....!"
mv cache cache_$(date +%d-%m-%Y_%H.%M.%S)
echo "Backup of cache folder taken successfully....!"
else
echo "cache folder not exists"
fi

postProcessingScript.name: ReleaseFile Post Process

properties.scriptBody:
cd ${p:ReleaseNotePath}

xi=$(ls ~*.xlsx 2> /dev/null | wc -l)

while [ "$xi" != "0" ]
do
new=(~*.*)
rm "$new"
xi=$(ls ~*.xlsx 2> /dev/null | wc -l)
done

count=(*.xlsx)
count=${#count[@]}

if [[ "$count" -gt 1 ]]; 
then

echo There are more than one ReleaseNote. Release note must be one...!
exit 1
fi

if [[ "$count" -eq 1 ]];
then
(
x=(*.xlsx)
y=" |'"
a=$(ls *.xlsx 2> /dev/null | wc -l)
if [[ "$x" =~ $y ]];
then
 mv "$x" "${x// /_}"
 echo ReleaseNote File Name:${x// /_}
elif [[ "$a" = "0" ]];
 then
 echo Release Note With Extention .xlsx is not present at location...!
 exit 1
else
 echo ReleaseNote File Name:$x
fi
)
fi
